1209 // When we have a pair of subscripts of the form [c1] and [c2],
1210 // where c1 and c2 are both loop invariant, we attack it using
1211 // the ZIV test. Basically, we test by comparing the two values,
1212 // but there are actually three possible results:
1213 // 1) the values are equal, so there's a dependence
1214 // 2) the values are different, so there's no dependence
1215 // 3) the values might be equal, so we have to assume a dependence.
